---
export const prerender = true;

const pageTitle = "Nuño review";
const pageDescription =
  "Private reference note from Nikita Sokolsky about working with Nuño.";
const themeColorLight = "#fcfbf8";
const themeColorDark = "#15120e";
const siteUrl =
  (Astro.site?.toString() ?? "https://sokolsky.me").replace(/\/$/, "");
const canonicalUrl = `${siteUrl}${Astro.url.pathname}`;
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow, noarchive" />
    <meta name="googlebot" content="noindex, nofollow, noarchive" />
    <meta name="referrer" content="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content={themeColorLight} />
    <meta name="theme-color" content={themeColorLight} media="(prefers-color-scheme: light)" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content={themeColorDark} media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)" />
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonicalUrl} />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="any" />
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="page">
      <article class="note" aria-label={pageTitle}>
        <p>
          Hi, I'm Nikita, an operator of a small niche business -
          <a href="https://getdatingphotos.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://getdatingphotos.com/</a>
        </p>

        <p>
          I've met Nuño after I did a photoshoot/restyle for him, and he
          convinced me to actually take the idea seriously. We've made a trade
          where in exchange for 5% of the business he'd let me use his
          face/photos on my public site & use him as a reference. Looking back I
          think this was an excellent deal, given that I underestimated how well
          known Nuño is in the Rationality-adjacent circles & how many people
          recognized his "glow up" as being insanely transformational.
        </p>

        <p>
          Other than his "personality rights" so to speak, his primary
          contribution was to hold me accountable in developing the business
          further and actually getting myself to do shit to expand it vs saying
          "fuck it". Mostly our interactions were in the form of me spamming Nuño
          at all hours of the day with various ideas/concerns I had & Nuño
          periodically responding to offer support/criticism and to push me to do
          better. I'm convinced that without his involvement it would've stayed
          frozen at
          <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20251212160448/https://getdatingphotos.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">the way it was in 2025</a>.
        </p>

        <p>
          Nuño has solid business acumen - 98th percentile or higher among ACX
          readers is my estimate. I mean, I might be wrong about this, but being
          convinced that this is true has so far done wonders for business
          development. He's also got solid contacts among other small-time
          businessmen (aka "powerseekers") that he's happy to introduce you to
          with and without prompting. I've been so happy with our arrangement
          that I've signed an extra deal with him to increase his share to 10% of
          the business in exchange for additional work to improve my deal flow.
        </p>

        <p>
          If you're the kind of guy who can trivially get into YC, then yeah,
          probably Nuño's not your guy, but for everyone else I can recommend him
          as a small-stake partner when starting out. Just remember that the
          initial valuation of any business is
          <a href="https://www.artlebedev.com/mandership/161/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">actually negative</a>,
          so in your negotiation avoid being overly greedy and trying to offer
          him something like 0.1% or something - without a sufficient stake I'm
          not confident he would be as helpful for you as he was for me.
        </p>

        <p>
          Disclaimer: I wrote this at Nuño's request, but I'm getting nothing in
          exchange, directly or indirectly. I'm also confident that if I wrote a
          much more negative perspective this wouldn't have damaged our
          relationship in any way & that he would've still shared this with you.
        </p>

        <footer class="written-date">
          Written down on July 3rd, 2026
        </footer>
      </article>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  :root {
    color-scheme: light dark;
    --bg: #fcfbf8;
    --card: #fffdf8;
    --text: #211a13;
    --muted: #786c5f;
    --link: #6d3b13;
    --link-hover: #3f220b;
    --border: rgba(55, 38, 22, 0.13);
    --shadow: 0 24px 80px rgba(45, 31, 18, 0.12);
  }

  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    :root {
      --bg: #15120e;
      --card: #1f1a14;
      --text: #f2eadf;
      --muted: #b9aa99;
      --link: #f0b36c;
      --link-hover: #ffd9a5;
      --border: rgba(255, 238, 212, 0.14);
      --shadow: 0 24px 80px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
    }
  }

  * {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  html {
    min-height: 100%;
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(183, 125, 58, 0.16), transparent 34rem),
      var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family:
      ui-serif,
      Georgia,
      Cambria,
      "Times New Roman",
      Times,
      serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.72;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
  }

  body {
    min-height: 100vh;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page {
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    padding: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 4rem);
  }

  .note {
    width: min(100%, 46rem);
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 28px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }

  p {
    margin: 0;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  p + p {
    margin-top: 1.45em;
  }

  .written-date {
    margin-top: 2.4rem;
    padding-top: 1.1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family:
      -apple-system,
      BlinkMacSystemFont,
      "Segoe UI",
      Roboto,
      Helvetica,
      Arial,
      sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--link);
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--link) 38%, transparent);
    text-decoration-thickness: 0.08em;
    text-underline-offset: 0.18em;
    transition:
      color 160ms ease,
      text-decoration-color 160ms ease;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--link-hover);
    text-decoration-color: currentColor;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    html {
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.68;
      background: var(--card);
    }

    .page {
      display: block;
      min-height: auto;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .note {
      width: 100%;
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 1.35rem 1.15rem 2rem;
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 0;
      box-shadow: none;
    }
  }
</style>
